Mainstreaming the General History of Africa (GHA) in education systems in Africa and around the world is both a tool and a catalyst for transformative education. By providing all learners with a broad understanding of African history, and promoting knowledge, skills, values and attitudes that defy hegemonic knowledge systems and racial biases, the GHA can contribute to forging a united, prosperous and peaceful Africa and world. 
In 2024-2025, efforts will focus on: 
a)	Developing a set of tools that comprise UNESCO’S Resource Pack for Teaching and Learning the General History of Africa (GHA), aimed at supporting the goal of mainstreaming the GHA into education systems in Africa and beyond;
b)	Piloting and supporting the contextualization of the GHA education tools at the regional and country level; 
c)	Strengthening the capacity of national education stakeholders to further integrate and mainstream the GHA into their curricula and education systems;

The objective of this RP, is to contribute to strengthening the capacity of the Ministry of Education and Training to implement the 10 year education plan that UNESCO Hanoi Office supported previously, with the ultimate aim to achieve quality education for all. 

Planned activities include: 
1) designing and preparing a new GPE funded System Strengthening detailed project document as a dual Grant Agent (with UNICEF) with special attention paid to provision of capacity development support in areas related to monitoring and evaluation of the education sector, and collection and analysis of data and evidence; 
2) provision of advice and support to strengthening the implementation of the National Strategy on Lifelong Learning (2021-2030) including by sharing international experiences and normative documents and by contributing to an expert workshop on the new legal framework under preparation; 
3) supporting monitoring of progress to achieve the SDG4 and to implement the ESD 2030 Country Initiative - this includes co—organization of a workshop to monitor the progress on ESD, following the consultation workshop co-organized with the Ministry of Education and Training in 2023.

